      • getOutputLayers

        public String[] getOutputLayers()
                         throws InvalidConfigurationException
        Determines which layers the annotator will create/update/delete annotations on.
        Specified by:
        getOutputLayers in class Annotator
        Returns:
        A list of layer IDs. In this case, the annotator has no task web-app for specifying an output layer, and doesn't update any layers, so this method returns an empty array.
        Throws:
        InvalidConfigurationException - If setTaskParameters(String) or Annotator.setSchema(Schema) have not yet been called.

      • transform

        public Graph transform​(Graph graph)
                throws TransformationException
        Transforms the graph. In this case, the graph is simply summarized, by counting all tokens of each word type, and printing out the result to stdout.
        Parameters:
        graph - The graph to transform.
        Returns:
        The changes introduced by the tranformation.
        Throws:
        TransformationException - If the transformation cannot be completed.
